posts.name: The Dog House
posts.note: The Dog House is a no-frills, cash-only eatery with counter seating, offering hot dogs, burgers, pizza, and cheesesteaks. Their foot long hot dogs or two in a soft roll with some tooth and an order of French fries will fill you right up.

posts.name: Go Fish!
posts.note: Go Fish! is a casual 40-seat restaurant with British theme featuring fish 'n' chips, toffee pudding, and other eats. The dish to order is the fish and chips (French fries) with a side order of curry sauce.
posts.cptn: Fish and chips (french fries for the Americans) with a side of curry sauce. Well worth the long drive home from Go Fish in Rehobooth Beach, DE

posts.name: Gus and Gus Place
posts.note: Gus and Gus Place is an iconic boardwalk standby with booth seating and a walk-up window offering burgers, fries, what looked like great fried chicken, and they even server breakfast. If you're not allergic to peanut oil you have to get an order of french fries. From The Rehoboth Foodie website 'When you think of the Rehoboth Beach Boardwalk, you can’t help but think of Gus & Gus’ Place. It’s as much a part of life around here as salt water taffy, the bandstand, parking tickets and summer evening happy hour on Baltimore Ave. Located at the foot of Wilmington Avenue, Gus & Gus’ has survived hurricanes, nor’easters and (so far) even the meddling “food police.”'

posts.name: Hopkins Farm Creamery
posts.note: Hopkins Farm Creamery's ice cream is made with local ingredients and sold from walk-up windows on a working dairy farm. You should get their salted caramel crunch which has nuts and large chocolate chip chunks.

posts.name: Maiale Deli and Salumeria
posts.note: Maiale Deli and Salumeria makes their own sausages, and you need to order the Thai curry chicken sausage or the Castro Cuban sandwich. From their website, 'Maiale believes that the difference between us and the rest are the unique combinations and flavors of sausage and salami. We make over 30 different varieties of fresh sausage and over ten different types of salami. We create the best-handcrafted salumi in Delaware.'

posts.name: Mrs. Robino's
posts.note: Mrs. Robino's is an old-school Italian restaurant in a circa-1940 renovated row house serving red-sauce classics. From their Facebook, 'Mrs. Robino’s Restaurant celebrates a love of traditional Italian cuisine, where every plate is served just as it was on grandma's table. Traditional Italian cooking is really about simplicity at its core. It's about having the freshest, liveliest ingredients, and bringing the flavor out of them through the masterful technique. It's what we've been doing for decades at Mrs. Robino’s Restaurant, and it's our dedication to traditional recipes that seems to keep generations of customers coming back.' If you go there, you need to order the Beef Braciole, which is braised in the oven for three hours and served with a side house-made spaghetti or an order of the Meat Ravioli.

posts.name: Vanderwende Farm Creamery
posts.note: Vanderwende Farm Creamery's ice cream is handcrafted and made right in Bridgeville Delaware. They only use the best quality ingredients to produce a rich and creamy ice-cream. They offer a wide variety of flavors, so there is sure to be one for you.
